vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
title: |md
  **Decision Tree: '/' Character — Division vs. Line Comment vs. Block Comment**
  *Maximal munch: '/' prefers the longer comment form when applicable*
| {near: top-center}
direction: down
entry: "advance() returns '/'" {
  style.fill: "#9B59B6"
  style.font-color: white
  style.bold: true
}
q1: "_match('/')\npeek next char == '/'?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#2980B9"
  style.font-color: white
  style.bold: true
}
q2: "_match('*')\npeek next char == '*'?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#2980B9"
  style.font-color: white
  style.bold: true
}
line_comment: "_scan_line_comment()" {
  style.fill: "#27AE60"
  style.font-color: white
  style.bold: true
}
block_comment: "_scan_block_comment()" {
  style.fill: "#27AE60"
  style.font-color: white
  style.bold: true
}
slash_token: "_make_token(SLASH)" {
  style.fill: "#E67E22"
  style.font-color: white
  style.bold: true
}
lc_detail: |md
  **Consumed so far:** `//`
  Loop: while not `is_at_end()` AND `peek() != '\n'`:
  → `advance()` (discard)
  Stop **before** consuming `\n`
  (left for main loop as whitespace)
| {
  style.fill: "#D5F5E3"
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
}
bc_success: "Return — comment closed\n(no token emitted)" {
  style.fill: "#D5F5E3"
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
  style.bold: true
}
bc_error: "Append Token(ERROR)\n@ opening '/' position\n(unterminated)" {
  style.fill: "#FADBD8"
  style.stroke: "#E74C3C"
  style.bold: true
}
bc_detail: |md
  **Consumed so far:** `/*`
  Loop: while not `is_at_end()`:
  - `peek() == '*'` → `advance()`
    - `peek() == '/'` → `advance()` → **return** ✓
    - else: continue (literal `*`)
  - else: `advance()` (discard; tracks `\n`)
  EOF exit → emit **ERROR**
| {
  style.fill: "#D5F5E3"
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
}
lc_out: "return\n(no token emitted)" {
  style.fill: "#D5F5E3"
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
  style.bold: true
}
slash_out: "return\n(SLASH token in stream)" {
  style.fill: "#FDEBD0"
  style.stroke: "#E67E22"
  style.bold: true
}
munch_note: |md
  **Maximal Munch Invariant**
  `'/'` prefers the **longer** form:
  - `//` beats `/` + `/`
  - `/*` beats `/` + `*`
  - Mirrors `=` preferring `==` over `ASSIGN + ASSIGN`
  Two-char check **must** precede
  `SINGLE_CHAR_TOKENS` lookup.
  `'/'` was **removed** from that dict.
| {
  near: bottom-right
  style.fill: "#EBF5FB"
  style.stroke: "#2980B9"
  style.font-size: 13
}
entry -> q1
q1 -> line_comment: "true\n_match('/') consumed\nsecond '/'" {
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
  style.bold: true
}
q1 -> q2: "false\nnext char ≠ '/'" {
  style.stroke: "#E74C3C"
  style.bold: true
}
q2 -> block_comment: "true\n_match('*') consumed\n'*'" {
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
  style.bold: true
}
q2 -> slash_token: "false\nnext char ≠ '*'" {
  style.stroke: "#E74C3C"
  style.bold: true
}
line_comment -> lc_detail
lc_detail -> lc_out
block_comment -> bc_detail
bc_detail -> bc_success
bc_detail -> bc_error: "EOF before '*/'" {
  style.stroke: "#E74C3C"
  style.stroke-dash: 4
}
slash_token -> slash_out